</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">++&nbsp;Xyank-Anastasakos&nbsp;Constant&nbsp;Time&nbsp;Sink</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">--&nbsp;Created&nbsp;by&nbsp;HammerMaiden!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="float: center; border: double 2px #0044a3; width: 570px; padding: 1px 15px; margin: 10px 10px 10px 40px; background-color: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h2 id="toc14"><span><span style="color:#0044a3"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span>Xyank-Anastasakos Constant Time Sink</span></span></h2>
<img src="http://fc07.deviantart.net/fs71/i/2014/321/4/3/xacts_01b_by_alanthos-d86q01z.png" width="570px" alt="xacts_01b_by_alanthos-d86q01z.png" class="image" /><br />
While this is a simpler, portable version of the items we know and love from SCP-2000, it can represent what the time sinks could actually look like if handled by the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/document-1780-wl">RCT-Δt</a> or their agents.
<p style="text-align: center;">Go to <a href="/scp-2000">SCP-2000</a>!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div class="image-container aligncenter"><img src="http://fc09.deviantart.net/fs71/f/2014/357/d/f/scpicon_by_alanthos-d8az7hg.png" width="100px" alt="scpicon_by_alanthos-d8az7hg.png" class="image" /></div>
<h1 id="toc15"><span><span style="color:#0044a3"><strong>SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES</strong></span></span></h1>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">++&nbsp;SCP-001,&nbsp;Roget's&nbsp;Proposal</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">--&nbsp;Created&nbsp;by&nbsp;Roget!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="float: center; border: double 2px #2b0000; width: 570px; padding: 1px 15px; margin: 10px 10px 10px 40px; background-color: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h2 id="toc16"><span><span style="color:#2b0000">SCP-001/Roget : KETER DUTY</span></span></h2>
<img src="http://th07.deviantart.net/fs71/PRE/f/2014/351/5/a/keter_duty___final_by_alanthos-d8a8ex1.png" width="570px" alt="keter_duty___final_by_alanthos-d8a8ex1.png" class="image" />
<p>SCP-001-Roget, the famed and infamous Keter Duty. It's not so bad when you get used to it, really. It's just every Keter ever in a research complex in Greece, sharing cells in pairs. And what pairings, dear lord, what pairings&#8230;</p>
<p>This blueprint is a liberal interpretation of the article proper made for the Third Art Exchange of 2014, but Roget seemed to like it, so I guess posting it here is kosher.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Go to <a href="/roget-s-proposal">Roget's Proposal</a>!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">++&nbsp;SCP-2722</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">--&nbsp;Created&nbsp;by&nbsp;Von&nbsp;Pincier!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="float: center; border: double 2px #2b0000; width: 570px; padding: 1px 15px; margin: 10px 10px 10px 40px; background-color: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h2 id="toc17"><span><span style="color:#2b0000">SCP- 2722 - SCPSS <em>Solidarity</em></span></span></h2>
<img src="http://fc02.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2014/335/c/7/2722_01_a_by_alanthos-d87qjcq.png" width="570px" alt="2722_01_a_by_alanthos-d87qjcq.png" class="image" />
<p>The general mapping plans of SCP-2722. I might add module plans eventually, but I've already dedicated far too much time to it; this project took me far too long, but I'm very happy with the result. The rest will have to wait.</p>
<p>Additionally, the reference to Area-08 as a Foundation dedicated space center puts a smile in my face. The salmon logo is a separate reference to the fact that Area-08 is placed in the Mid-Atlantic, but that's a story for a different time.</p>
<p>Thanks to everyone on chat for their feedback on this piece.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Go to <a href="/scp-2722">SCP-2722</a>!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
